defaultI am particularly concerned about some clauses in the bill regarding rights of way.
default&#xa0;
defaultAs a regular walker in the Peak District I am distressed at the damage, erosion, noise and general annoyance caused by ‘off roaders’ ie motor cycles and 4 wd vehicles using the ancient tracks and byways.  This is a very serious problem.
default&#xa0;
defaultOff roaders claim that they are permitted to use UUCR’s (green lanes) and BOAT’s (by-ways open to all traffic) without any regard to the effect this has on the countryside or the enjoyment of the majority of people using the countryside.
default&#xa0;
defaultThese ancient tracks and byways may historically have been used for wheeled vehicles – and their continued use for agricultural vehicles is reasonable – but they were not built or ever intended to be used by mechanical vehicles and the state of many of them is now deplorable.
default&#xa0;
defaultI strongly support any measure that would
default&#xa0;
